2869 /// See if \p I should be considered for address type promotion. We check if \p
2870 /// I is a sext with right type and used in memory accesses. If it used in a
2871 /// "complex" getelementptr, we allow it to be promoted without finding other
2872 /// sext instructions that sign extended the same initial value. A getelementptr
2873 /// is considered as "complex" if it has more than 2 operands.
2874 bool AArch64TTIImpl::shouldConsiderAddressTypePromotion(
2875  const Instruction &I, bool &AllowPromotionWithoutCommonHeader) {
2876  bool Considerable = false;
2877  AllowPromotionWithoutCommonHeader = false;
2878  if (!isa<SExtInst>(&I))
2879  return false;
2880  Type *ConsideredSExtType =
2881  Type::getInt64Ty(I.getParent()->getParent()->getContext());
2882  if (I.getType() != ConsideredSExtType)
2883  return false;
2884  // See if the sext is the one with the right type and used in at least one
2885  // GetElementPtrInst.
2886  for (const User *U : I.users()) {
2887  if (const GetElementPtrInst *GEPInst = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(U)) {
2888  Considerable = true;
2889  // A getelementptr is considered as "complex" if it has more than 2
2890  // operands. We will promote a SExt used in such complex GEP as we
2891  // expect some computation to be merged if they are done on 64 bits.
2892  if (GEPInst->getNumOperands() > 2) {
2893  AllowPromotionWithoutCommonHeader = true;
2894  break;
2895  }
2896  }
2897  }
2898  return Considerable;
2899 }

2916  case RecurKind::SMin:
2917  case RecurKind::SMax:

2931 InstructionCost
2932 AArch64TTIImpl::getMinMaxReductionCost(VectorType *Ty, VectorType *CondTy,
2933  bool IsUnsigned,
2934  TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind) {

2936

2957 InstructionCost AArch64TTIImpl::getArithmeticReductionCostSVE(
2958  unsigned Opcode, VectorType *ValTy, TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind) {
2959  std::pair<InstructionCost, MVT> LT = getTypeLegalizationCost(ValTy);
2960  InstructionCost LegalizationCost = 0;
2961  if (LT.first > 1) {
2962  Type *LegalVTy = EVT(LT.second).getTypeForEVT(ValTy->getContext());
2963  LegalizationCost = getArithmeticInstrCost(Opcode, LegalVTy, CostKind);
2964  LegalizationCost *= LT.first - 1;
2965  }
2966 
2967  int ISD = TLI->InstructionOpcodeToISD(Opcode);
2968  assert(ISD && "Invalid opcode");
2969  // Add the final reduction cost for the legal horizontal reduction
2970  switch (ISD) {
2971  case ISD::ADD:
2972  case ISD::AND:
2973  case ISD::OR:
2974  case ISD::XOR:
2975  case ISD::FADD:
2976  return LegalizationCost + 2;
2977  default:
2978  return InstructionCost::getInvalid();
2979  }

2982 InstructionCost
2983 AArch64TTIImpl::getArithmeticReductionCost(unsigned Opcode, VectorType *ValTy,
2984  std::optional<FastMathFlags> FMF,
2985  TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind) {
2986  if (TTI::requiresOrderedReduction(FMF)) {
2987  if (auto *FixedVTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(ValTy)) {
2988  InstructionCost BaseCost =
2989  BaseT::getArithmeticReductionCost(Opcode, ValTy, FMF, CostKind);
2990  // Add on extra cost to reflect the extra overhead on some CPUs. We still
2991  // end up vectorizing for more computationally intensive loops.
2992  return BaseCost + FixedVTy->getNumElements();
2993  }
2994 
2995  if (Opcode != Instruction::FAdd)
2996  return InstructionCost::getInvalid();
2997 
2998  auto *VTy = cast<ScalableVectorType>(ValTy);
2999  InstructionCost Cost =
3000  getArithmeticInstrCost(Opcode, VTy->getScalarType(), CostKind);
3001  Cost *= getMaxNumElements(VTy->getElementCount());
3002  return Cost;
3003  }
3004 
3005  if (isa<ScalableVectorType>(ValTy))
3006  return getArithmeticReductionCostSVE(Opcode, ValTy, CostKind);
3007 
3008  std::pair<InstructionCost, MVT> LT = getTypeLegalizationCost(ValTy);
3009  MVT MTy = LT.second;
3010  int ISD = TLI->InstructionOpcodeToISD(Opcode);
3011  assert(ISD && "Invalid opcode");
3012 
3013  // Horizontal adds can use the 'addv' instruction. We model the cost of these
3014  // instructions as twice a normal vector add, plus 1 for each legalization
3015  // step (LT.first). This is the only arithmetic vector reduction operation for
3016  // which we have an instruction.
3017  // OR, XOR and AND costs should match the codegen from:
3018  // OR: llvm/test/CodeGen/AArch64/reduce-or.ll
3019  // XOR: llvm/test/CodeGen/AArch64/reduce-xor.ll
3020  // AND: llvm/test/CodeGen/AArch64/reduce-and.ll
3021  static const CostTblEntry CostTblNoPairwise[]{
3022  {ISD::ADD, MVT::v8i8, 2},
3023  {ISD::ADD, MVT::v16i8, 2},
3024  {ISD::ADD, MVT::v4i16, 2},
3025  {ISD::ADD, MVT::v8i16, 2},
3026  {ISD::ADD, MVT::v4i32, 2},
3027  {ISD::ADD, MVT::v2i64, 2},
3028  {ISD::OR, MVT::v8i8, 15},
3029  {ISD::OR, MVT::v16i8, 17},
3030  {ISD::OR, MVT::v4i16, 7},
3031  {ISD::OR, MVT::v8i16, 9},
3032  {ISD::OR, MVT::v2i32, 3},
3033  {ISD::OR, MVT::v4i32, 5},
3034  {ISD::OR, MVT::v2i64, 3},
3035  {ISD::XOR, MVT::v8i8, 15},
3036  {ISD::XOR, MVT::v16i8, 17},
3037  {ISD::XOR, MVT::v4i16, 7},
3038  {ISD::XOR, MVT::v8i16, 9},
3039  {ISD::XOR, MVT::v2i32, 3},
3040  {ISD::XOR, MVT::v4i32, 5},
3041  {ISD::XOR, MVT::v2i64, 3},
3042  {ISD::AND, MVT::v8i8, 15},
3043  {ISD::AND, MVT::v16i8, 17},
3044  {ISD::AND, MVT::v4i16, 7},
3045  {ISD::AND, MVT::v8i16, 9},
3046  {ISD::AND, MVT::v2i32, 3},
3047  {ISD::AND, MVT::v4i32, 5},
3048  {ISD::AND, MVT::v2i64, 3},
3049  };
3050  switch (ISD) {
3051  default:
3052  break;
3053  case ISD::ADD:
3054  if (const auto *Entry = CostTableLookup(CostTblNoPairwise, ISD, MTy))
3055  return (LT.first - 1) + Entry->Cost;
3056  break;
3057  case ISD::XOR:
3058  case ISD::AND:
3059  case ISD::OR:
3060  const auto *Entry = CostTableLookup(CostTblNoPairwise, ISD, MTy);
3061  if (!Entry)
3062  break;
3063  auto *ValVTy = cast<FixedVectorType>(ValTy);
3064  if (!ValVTy->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(1) &&
3065  MTy.getVectorNumElements() <= ValVTy->getNumElements() &&
3066  isPowerOf2_32(ValVTy->getNumElements())) {
3067  InstructionCost ExtraCost = 0;
3068  if (LT.first != 1) {
3069  // Type needs to be split, so there is an extra cost of LT.first - 1
3070  // arithmetic ops.
3071  auto *Ty = FixedVectorType::get(ValTy->getElementType(),
3072  MTy.getVectorNumElements());
3073  ExtraCost = getArithmeticInstrCost(Opcode, Ty, CostKind);
3074  ExtraCost *= LT.first - 1;
3075  }
3076  return Entry->Cost + ExtraCost;
3077  }
3078  break;
3079  }
3080  return BaseT::getArithmeticReductionCost(Opcode, ValTy, FMF, CostKind);
3081 }

3083 InstructionCost AArch64TTIImpl::getSpliceCost(VectorType *Tp, int Index) {
3084  static const CostTblEntry ShuffleTbl[] = {
3085  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv16i8, 1 },
3086  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv8i16, 1 },
3087  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv4i32, 1 },
3088  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv2i64, 1 },
3089  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv2f16, 1 },
3090  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv4f16, 1 },
3091  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv8f16, 1 },
3092  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv2bf16, 1 },
3093  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv4bf16, 1 },
3094  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv8bf16, 1 },
3095  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv2f32, 1 },
3096  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv4f32, 1 },
3097  { TTI::SK_Splice, MVT::nxv2f64, 1 },
3098  };
3099 
3100  // The code-generator is currently not able to handle scalable vectors
3101  // of <vscale x 1 x eltty> yet, so return an invalid cost to avoid selecting
3102  // it. This change will be removed when code-generation for these types is
3103  // sufficiently reliable.
3104  if (Tp->getElementCount() == ElementCount::getScalable(1))
3105  return InstructionCost::getInvalid();
3106 
3107  std::pair<InstructionCost, MVT> LT = getTypeLegalizationCost(Tp);
3108  Type *LegalVTy = EVT(LT.second).getTypeForEVT(Tp->getContext());
3109  TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind = TTI::TCK_RecipThroughput;
3110  EVT PromotedVT = LT.second.getScalarType() == MVT::i1
3111  ? TLI->getPromotedVTForPredicate(EVT(LT.second))
3112  : LT.second;
3113  Type *PromotedVTy = EVT(PromotedVT).getTypeForEVT(Tp->getContext());
3114  InstructionCost LegalizationCost = 0;
3115  if (Index < 0) {
3116  LegalizationCost =
3117  getCmpSelInstrCost(Instruction::ICmp, PromotedVTy, PromotedVTy,
3118  CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE, CostKind) +
3119  getCmpSelInstrCost(Instruction::Select, PromotedVTy, LegalVTy,
3120  CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE, CostKind);
3121  }
3122 
3123  // Predicated splice are promoted when lowering. See AArch64ISelLowering.cpp
3124  // Cost performed on a promoted type.
3125  if (LT.second.getScalarType() == MVT::i1) {
3126  LegalizationCost +=
3127  getCastInstrCost(Instruction::ZExt, PromotedVTy, LegalVTy,
3128  TTI::CastContextHint::None, CostKind) +
3129  getCastInstrCost(Instruction::Trunc, LegalVTy, PromotedVTy,
3130  TTI::CastContextHint::None, CostKind);
3131  }
3132  const auto *Entry =
3133  CostTableLookup(ShuffleTbl, TTI::SK_Splice, PromotedVT.getSimpleVT());
3134  assert(Entry && "Illegal Type for Splice");
3135  LegalizationCost += Entry->Cost;
3136  return LegalizationCost * LT.first;
3137 }

3139 InstructionCost AArch64TTIImpl::getShuffleCost(TTI::ShuffleKind Kind,
3140  VectorType *Tp,
3141  ArrayRef<int> Mask,
3142  TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind,
3143  int Index, VectorType *SubTp,
3144  ArrayRef<const Value *> Args) {
3145  std::pair<InstructionCost, MVT> LT = getTypeLegalizationCost(Tp);
3146  // If we have a Mask, and the LT is being legalized somehow, split the Mask
3147  // into smaller vectors and sum the cost of each shuffle.
3148  if (!Mask.empty() && isa<FixedVectorType>(Tp) && LT.second.isVector() &&
3149  Tp->getScalarSizeInBits() == LT.second.getScalarSizeInBits() &&
3150  cast<FixedVectorType>(Tp)->getNumElements() >
3151  LT.second.getVectorNumElements() &&
3152  !Index && !SubTp) {
3153  unsigned TpNumElts = cast<FixedVectorType>(Tp)->getNumElements();
3154  assert(Mask.size() == TpNumElts && "Expected Mask and Tp size to match!");
3155  unsigned LTNumElts = LT.second.getVectorNumElements();
3156  unsigned NumVecs = (TpNumElts + LTNumElts - 1) / LTNumElts;
3157  VectorType *NTp =
3158  VectorType::get(Tp->getScalarType(), LT.second.getVectorElementCount());
3159  InstructionCost Cost;
3160  for (unsigned N = 0; N < NumVecs; N++) {
3161  SmallVector<int> NMask;
3162  // Split the existing mask into chunks of size LTNumElts. Track the source
3163  // sub-vectors to ensure the result has at most 2 inputs.
3164  unsigned Source1, Source2;
3165  unsigned NumSources = 0;
3166  for (unsigned E = 0; E < LTNumElts; E++) {
3167  int MaskElt = (N * LTNumElts + E < TpNumElts) ? Mask[N * LTNumElts + E]
3168  : UndefMaskElem;
3169  if (MaskElt < 0) {
3170  NMask.push_back(UndefMaskElem);
3171  continue;
3172  }
3173 
3174  // Calculate which source from the input this comes from and whether it
3175  // is new to us.
3176  unsigned Source = MaskElt / LTNumElts;
3177  if (NumSources == 0) {
3178  Source1 = Source;
3179  NumSources = 1;
3180  } else if (NumSources == 1 && Source != Source1) {
3181  Source2 = Source;
3182  NumSources = 2;
3183  } else if (NumSources >= 2 && Source != Source1 && Source != Source2) {
3184  NumSources++;
3185  }
3186 
3187  // Add to the new mask. For the NumSources>2 case these are not correct,
3188  // but are only used for the modular lane number.
3189  if (Source == Source1)
3190  NMask.push_back(MaskElt % LTNumElts);
3191  else if (Source == Source2)
3192  NMask.push_back(MaskElt % LTNumElts + LTNumElts);
3193  else
3194  NMask.push_back(MaskElt % LTNumElts);
3195  }
3196  // If the sub-mask has at most 2 input sub-vectors then re-cost it using
3197  // getShuffleCost. If not then cost it using the worst case.
3198  if (NumSources <= 2)
3199  Cost += getShuffleCost(NumSources <= 1 ? TTI::SK_PermuteSingleSrc
3200  : TTI::SK_PermuteTwoSrc,
3201  NTp, NMask, CostKind, 0, nullptr, Args);
3202  else if (any_of(enumerate(NMask), [&](const auto &ME) {
3203  return ME.value() % LTNumElts == ME.index();
3204  }))
3205  Cost += LTNumElts - 1;
3206  else
3207  Cost += LTNumElts;
3208  }
3209  return Cost;
3210  }
3211 
3212  Kind = improveShuffleKindFromMask(Kind, Mask);
3213 
3214  // Check for broadcast loads.
3215  if (Kind == TTI::SK_Broadcast) {
3216  bool IsLoad = !Args.empty() && isa<LoadInst>(Args[0]);
3217  if (IsLoad && LT.second.isVector() &&
3218  isLegalBroadcastLoad(Tp->getElementType(),
3219  LT.second.getVectorElementCount()))

3221  }

3226  (Tp->getScalarSizeInBits() == 16 || Tp->getScalarSizeInBits() == 32) &&
3227  all_of(Mask, [](int E) { return E < 8; }))

3365  return BaseT::getShuffleCost(Kind, Tp, Mask, CostKind, Index, SubTp);
3366 }

3368 bool AArch64TTIImpl::preferPredicateOverEpilogue(
3369  Loop *L, LoopInfo *LI, ScalarEvolution &SE, AssumptionCache &AC,
3370  TargetLibraryInfo *TLI, DominatorTree *DT, LoopVectorizationLegality *LVL,
3371  InterleavedAccessInfo *IAI) {
3372  if (!ST->hasSVE() || TailFoldingKindLoc == TailFoldingKind::TFDisabled)
3373  return false;
3374 
3375  // We don't currently support vectorisation with interleaving for SVE - with
3376  // such loops we're better off not using tail-folding. This gives us a chance
3377  // to fall back on fixed-width vectorisation using NEON's ld2/st2/etc.
3378  if (IAI->hasGroups())
3379  return false;
3380 
3381  TailFoldingKind Required; // Defaults to 0.
3382  if (LVL->getReductionVars().size())
3383  Required.add(TailFoldingKind::TFReductions);
3384  if (LVL->getFixedOrderRecurrences().size())
3385  Required.add(TailFoldingKind::TFRecurrences);
3386  if (!Required)
3387  Required.add(TailFoldingKind::TFSimple);
3388 
3389  return (TailFoldingKindLoc & Required) == Required;
3390 }

3394  int64_t BaseOffset, bool HasBaseReg,
3395  int64_t Scale, unsigned AddrSpace) const {
3396  // Scaling factors are not free at all.
3397  // Operands | Rt Latency
3398  // -------------------------------------------
3399  // Rt, [Xn, Xm] | 4
3400  // -------------------------------------------
3401  // Rt, [Xn, Xm, lsl #imm] | Rn: 4 Rm: 5
3402  // Rt, [Xn, Wm, <extend> #imm] |
3403  TargetLoweringBase::AddrMode AM;
3404  AM.BaseGV = BaseGV;
3405  AM.BaseOffs = BaseOffset;
3406  AM.HasBaseReg = HasBaseReg;
3407  AM.Scale = Scale;
3408  if (getTLI()->isLegalAddressingMode(DL, AM, Ty, AddrSpace))
3409  // Scale represents reg2 * scale, thus account for 1 if
3410  // it is not equal to 0 or 1.
3411  return AM.Scale != 0 && AM.Scale != 1;
3412  return -1;
3413 }
